So, higher up you said that the soup was made from goat cream and shredded mushrooms, but in the recipe it is made from goat butter and chopped mushrooms. So those should probably be equalized. I know butter is made from cream but you wouldn't say that it was made from cream if it was actually made from butter, unless the instructions were to personally turn the cream into butter before making the soup which they aren't. And making goat butter isn't as easy for regular people as making cow butter. Logistically, goat butter is more readily available than goat cream, so that might be the better one to stick with for a few reasons. As for chopped vs shredded, that's just a texture thing, roughly chopped would give you a chunkier soup and shredded would be less chunky.







